listitem.simpara:
Prior to UCS 3.2 a terminal resolution of 800x600 pixels with a colour
depth of 16 bits has been used as default (grub/vga=788).  During the update to UCS
3.2 the color depth switches from 16 to 24 bits (grub/vga=789) if the default settings
are still set.  The old state may be regained by setting the &ucsUCRV;
grub/vga=788. To prevent this change during the update, set the &ucsUCRV;
update32/grub/changecolordepth=no prior to the update (Bug 32634).

Added support for denying client access based on IP addresses, configurable via &ucsUCRV;
cups/printmode/hosts/none. This functionality is needed for UCS@School.
(Bug 32055).

The &ucsUCRV; windows/wins-server and &ucsUCRV;
windows/wins-support are now set in the Samba joinscript
(Bug 31814, Bug 32745).

&ucsUCRV; windows/wins-server and &ucsUCRV;
windows/wins-support are now initialized during join
(Bug 30813, Bug 32745).
